<br>
(Pause here while head spins at the idea of the bomb racking and loading mechanisms with 1500 ton PU’s rattling along it like tins in a canning plant then to be spat out the back at one per second!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Imagine a hemisphere 400 meters in diameter and 250 meters high. You could stack half a dozen USS Nimitses in that!<br>
<br>
Say 2 million tons for the pusher plate, say 3 million tons for NPU’s * this would leave 3 million tons for the rest of the ships structure, life support crew compartments etc and deliverable payload.<br>
<br>
(*For a round trip. A one way journey would need less NPU's therefore a greater payload would be possible. perhaps a million tons greater!)<br>
<br>
It was estimated that something like this could deliver around 1.5 million tons of payload to anywhere in the solar system at 5c/lb (1960 money)<br>
<br>
I'll just say that again (My edit)<br>
<br>
5c/Lb<br>
<br>
The explosive force required would not be excessive for a remote ground launch site and (surprisingly) the launch of a super-orion would not produce any more fallout than the launch of a small one (the amount of fissionable material used is about the same in each case) added to that if we have 1500 ton PU’s to play with we may be able to use exotic triggers such as antimatter for the first 1-200 or so Pus (the ones fired in the atmosphere) to allow pure fusion and greatly reduced fallout. “Dirty” bombs would only be used once we are in space.<br>
<br>
The launch of a monster like this would be the most awesome sight human eyes have ever seen, I can’t wait!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smileroll --><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein_1/Smilies_klein_1_1/youpiaa.gif ALT=":smileroll"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I can’t see ships of this size being “Common” but half a dozen of these could be launched on one-way journeys to various parts of the solar system to fulfil specific functions for example;<br>
<br>
1)An Ore processing and manufacturing facility CW crew accommodation in the asteroid belt.<br>
 <br>
2)A fuel processing and chemical plant around Saturn providing water, hydrogen and oxygen for the space stations and the smaller chemical and NTR’s that will be needed.<br>
<br>
3)A dedicated shipyard for the repair and construction of smaller ships, Orion class or otherwise (this could be launched C/W a compliment of smaller ships already on board)<br>
<br>
In all cases the pusher plates could be dismantled on arrival at the various destinations and used for construction and manufacture so nothing would be wasted.<br>
<br>
Im sure I could think of others. The launch of half a dozen of these to specific destinations could shave a century off the colonisation of space (Possibly more) and save huge amounts of money and a great number of lives.<br>
<br>
